1. apt-get update
2. Install docker
3. Restart pc after docker is installed
12. Install docker-compose
	sudo apt-get update
	sudo apt-get install docker-compose-plugin
13. Create mysql_data dir in /opt/
4. Pull all docker images
	4.a. guacamole
	4.b. guacd
	4.c. mysql
5. Run sudo docker compose config
	make sure any changes made are good
5. Run sudo docker compose up -d
6. Connect into docker mysql interactive bash shell
	2.a: sudo docker exec -it homelab-mysql bash
7. Connect to mysql
	7.a: mysql -u root -p
	7.b.: Then enter your password when prompted
8. Run the following commands to initalize the databases and permissions

	CREATE DATABASE guacamole_db;

	CREATE USER 'guacamole_user'@'localhost' IDENTIFIED BY 'Pointing!Diagnosis3!Anemia';
	CREATE USER 'guacadmin'@'localhost' IDENTIFIED BY 'guacadmin';
	CREATE USER 'homelab-guac'@'localhost' IDENTIFIED BY 'Pointing!Diagnosis3!Anemia';
	CREATE USER 'admin'@'localhost' IDENTIFIED BY 'Pointing!Diagnosis3!Anemia';
	
	GRANT SELECT,INSERT,UPDATE,DELETE ON guacamole_db.* TO 'homelab-guac'@'localhost';
	GRANT SELECT,INSERT,UPDATE,DELETE ON guacamole_db.* TO 'guacamole_user'@'localhost';
	GRANT SELECT,INSERT,UPDATE,DELETE ON guacamole_db.* TO 'guacadmin'@'localhost';
	GRANT SELECT,INSERT,UPDATE,DELETE ON guacamole_db.* TO 'admin'@'localhost';

	FLUSH PRIVILEGES;

	connect guacamole_db

9. Run the script provided by guacamole to initialize the database tables
12. Enable docker on boot
	12.a: sudo systemctl enable docker
	
13. Install docker cloudflare tunnel


Useful Commands:
1. sudo docker container ls --all
2. sudo docker container stop some-mysql
3. sudo docker container rm some-mysql
4. sudo docker logs homelab-mysql
5. sudo docker inspect homelab-mysql

Useful Sites:
1. https://www.composerize.com/

